  "narrative": {
    "intro": "Department of Energy contract obligations total $45.7B in FY2026 to date, spread across 3,729 awards with an average award size of $12.3M. Obligations fell 5.8% year over year and current-year totals are partial (fiscal year to date). Historical annual obligations show growth from $37.7B in FY21 to $48.5B in FY25, with FY26 at $45.7B. The largest single NAICS category in FY2026 to date is Facilities Support Services at $23.2B, followed by research and development lines that together account for multiple entries including $6.9B and $3.4B. Remediation Services and chemical manufacturing also appear among the top categories at $2.9B and $2.8B, respectively. Vendor concentration is notable: TRIAD NATIONAL SECURITY, LLC has $5.1B in obligations and NATIONAL TECHNOLOGY & ENGINEERING SOLUTIONS OF SANDIA, LLC has $4.5B, with several national lab contractors and systems integrators reporting obligations in the $1.6B–$3.3B range. These figures reflect contract obligations recorded through the current fiscal year to date.",
    "sections": [
      {
        "heading": "How has DOE contract spending changed over recent years?",
        "body": "Obligations rose from $37.7B in FY21 to $48.5B in FY25 and are $45.7B in FY26 to date. Obligations fell 5.8% year over year and the FY2026 total is partial (fiscal year to date)."
      },
      {
        "heading": "Which categories and vendors dominate DOE contracting in FY2026 to date?",
        "body": "Facilities Support Services is the largest category at $23.2B, with multiple research and development categories totaling entries of $6.9B, $3.4B, and $776M. TRIAD NATIONAL SECURITY, LLC leads vendors with $5.1B, followed by NATIONAL TECHNOLOGY & ENGINEERING SOLUTIONS OF SANDIA, LLC at $4.5B and several other contractors with obligations between $1.6B and $3.3B."
      }
    ]
